  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "2. In a large skillet, cook the bacon slices until crispy. Set aside.",
    "3. Cut the corn tortillas into quarters and place on a baking sheet.",
    "4. Drizzle with oil and season with salt. Bake for 5-7 minutes, or until crispy.",
    "5. In a large bowl, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise, and diced olives.",
    "6. Stir in the chopped cilantro and sliced red onion.",
    "7. Spoon the sour cream mixture onto a tortilla quarter and top with crispy bacon.",
    "8. Add a sprinkle of cheddar cheese and a few slices of jalapeño.",
    "9. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
